cs.GR, cs.CV, cs.HC, cs.AI, cs.LG 

This paper involves generating gaits for virtual characters and extracting gait features based on visual perception and psychology literature. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the Graphics (cs.GR) and Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves a user study to establish a data-driven dominance mapping, which falls under the Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) sub-category. The paper also uses machine learning algorithms to classify dominance traits, which falls under the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories.
